In this case, we see that the stack expanded by 0x4 from 1 to 2 (i.e. when `j` was declared). However, during the function call, the address contracted (from output 2 to 3 by 0x2c). Based on the answer (here)[https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1677415/does-stack-grow-upward-or-downward], I understand that the stack grows either upwards or downwards based on the architecture.  
